@ClockworkKat you will need a NFC tag writer app like "NCF Tools" on android and a service to run LNURL-withdraw like https://strike.army.

Setup a LNURL-withdraw address at strike.army with a relatively conservative limit. (Like daily spend of ~$10, max spend of ~$100) In the NFC writer app add a custom URI that starts with "lightning:" + your LNURL-withdraw. Should look something like "lightning:LNURL1DF345...." Then write that data to an NFC NTAG 215 type of chip/card using the app.

When you want to make an lightning payment with NFC, have someone open Wallet or Satoshi or Breeze and enter in a sat amount to receive less than $10. You can just tap your tag/card and will pay the invoice from the account setup with strike.army.

